Hoshi Corbyn BOT 02-Jul-21 03:41 PM
Yeah, I gotta do this. Hoshi heard the announcement, of course. It would have been impossible not to hear it. She couldn't believe it; she understood the rules of the game well, but she didn't think someone would actually kill BECAUSE of the rules and the motive. ...though that does bring into question what she thought would have ended the motive regardless. She did want it to end (and her wish was granted), but not like this. Maybe she thought it would disappear on its own. How naïve. Right right, the body. She rushed in... and immediately froze. It's not as if the body was in horrible shape - honestly, this was one of the more tamer first chapters (though that's not an insult to Kev, just a simple fact), but... ...believe it or not, Hoshi had never seen a dead, murdered body before. At least, not like this. She didn't understand it; she didn't comprehend it. How was she supposed to understand it? Someone killed. Someone did it. Someone took away another person's life. Hoshi (somewhat awkwardly) would eventually try to feel for Kuno's pulse. Nothing. The body felt cold. She stepped back. Who... who could have done this? And why? And why him? She was... secretly thankful that it wasn't anyone too close to her, but Kuno... well, he didn't seem like a bad kid at all. She would have loved to talk to him about stuff, and, well... ... ...she continued to stand there for quite some time, unsure of what to do and frozen with her thoughts.
...eh, let's continue this. She eventually took a quick look around the room. It... wasn't a pleasant sight. She got the feeling she should be investigating and trying to solve this case. I mean, according to the rules, there was a trial, right? If the trial was to find whoever this 'blackened' is - and it seemed like it was suggesting how the rules were worded - then she should be ready for it. ...but she couldn't. She felt weak and alone - everyone else either seemed fully ready to deal with a body and murder or already left. She was the only one still here, just trying to process what happened. She wished she could go back home. She really did. It would mean dealing with her parents, yes, but it would also mean more safety. But... home seemed so far away now. ... Eventually, she regained her composure just a little bit. Her dreams weren't going to be pleasant at all - she had a feeling she would dream being attacked and ending up like that body for weeks - but that was just a part of life, she supposed. And looking at her Monopad, it seemed to be buzzing off with new notifications... 'Truth Bullets', which were essentially evidence, and 'Monokuma Files', which were autopsies of sorts. She figured everyone had already found everything at this point, so she could use those two to try to find out who did it. She also realized, this entire time, she was crying. Huh. It's funny what you don't notice. Regardless, she said, rather shakily: "I-I'm sorry Kuno... y-you didn't deserve this. I-I hope you're doing safe u-up there, but... I-I know we'll try to find out w-who did this, and... h-hopefully, knowing your murderer will g-give you some peace." ...and with that, she left the room.
